rch seine Darstellung in den beiden Stuart Little-Filmen bekannt und durch den Kinderfilm Der kleine Vampir aus dem Jahr 2000.","name":"","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"FR","iso_639_1":"fr","name":"Français","english_name":"French","data":{"biography":"","name":"","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"JP","iso_639_1":"ja","name":"日本語","english_name":"Japanese","data":{"biography":"","name":"ジョナサン・リプニッキ","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"CN","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"","name":"乔纳森·利普尼基","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"HK","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"","name":"喬納森·利普尼基","primary":false}}]}},"person_235548_translations":{"at":1773688723020,"data":{"id":235548,"translations":[{"iso_3166_1":"US","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English","english_name":"English","data":{"biography":"​From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia.  \n\nKevin Downes is an American actor, writer, producer and director. Downes grew up in Visalia, 3 hours north of Los Angeles. Most of the Christians films he participated in were shot there.\n\nHe has over 15 years’ writing, directing, acting and producing experience, much of it in the faith-based market. His vision is to produce quality motion pictures to share strong messages of hope, faith and love that come through a personal relationship with God. The movie Mercy Streets which he produced  was nominated for the Best Family Film Award.\n\nKevin lives in Visalia, California with his wife Catherine and dog Darby. Kevin Downes is the younger brother of producer Bobby Downes who is the founder and CEO of ChristianCinema.com. In 2003, Kevin wrote, produced, directed and starred in Six: The Mark Unleashed opposite Stephen Baldwin, Eric Roberts, David A.R. White and Jeffrey Dean Morgan. The movie was released wide in June 2004.\n\nDescription above from the Wikipedia article Kevin Downes,  licensed under CC-BY-SA, full list of contributors on Wikipedia.","name":"Kevin Downes","primary":true}},{"iso_3166_1":"IT","iso_639_1":"it","name":"Italiano","english_name":"Italian","data":{"biography":"","name":"","primary":false}}]}},"person_77933_translations":{"at":1773688723457,"data":{"id":77933,"translations":[{"iso_3166_1":"US","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English","english_name":"English","data":{"biography":"Yamaguchi Yuriko was born November 21, 1965 in Osaka Prefecture, Japan. She is a voice actress (seiyuu). Yuriko was initially part of 81 Produce, but went freelance, then joined Vi-Vo. Currently she affiliated with Aoni Production. Her real name is written a bit differently (山口百里子), but read the same way.\n\nEiko Jinno and Yoshiko Nikaidou are aliases used by Yamaguchi Yuriko for adult games and anime.","name":"Yuriko Yamaguchi","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"CN","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"山口由里子，1965年11月21日出生于大阪府，日本女性声优。本名山口百里子（やまぐち ゆりこ）。代表作品有《 海贼王》，《 新世纪福音战士》。","name":"山口由里子","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"JP","iso_639_1":"ja","name":"日本語","english_name":"Japanese","data":{"biography":"","name":"山口由里子","primary":true}},{"iso_3166_1":"TW","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"","name":"山口由里子","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"FR","iso_639_1":"fr","name":"Français","english_name":"French","data":{"biography":"","name":"Yuriko Yamaguchi","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"KR","iso_639_1":"ko","name":"한국어/조선말","english_name":"Korean","data":{"biography":"","name":"야마구치 유리코","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"TH","iso_639_1":"th","name":"ภาษาไทย","english_name":"Thai","data":{"biography":"","name":"ยูริโกะ ยะมะงุชิ","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"CZ","iso_639_1":"cs","name":"Český","english_name":"Czech","data":{"biography":"","name":"Juriko Jamaguči","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"BR","iso_639_1":"pt","name":"Português","english_name":"Portuguese","data":{"biography":"","name":"Yuriko Yamaguchi","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"IR","iso_639_1":